US President Joe Biden sits in the Oval Office at the White House in Washington DC, after being sworn in at the US Capitol. AFP/Jim Watson WASHINGTON - President Joe Biden said that outgoing president Donald Trump had left him a "very generous" letter in the Oval Office, in keeping with tradition. "The president wrote a very generous letter," Biden told reporters at the White House. READ: Donald Trump left a letter for Joe Biden: spokesman "Because it's private, I will not talk about it until I talk to him," he said. It was unclear until Wednesday whether Trump would maintain the tradition of outgoing presidents leaving notes for their successors. He opted to skip Biden's inauguration and never formally congratulated him on his election win.